<item>
            <title>[LU-17665] LNet: lock primary NID only on a peer constructed by Lustre</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17665</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Primary NID locking is useful when client is connecting to a server and peer representation is provided to LNet by Lustre via LNetAddPeer API - as interpreted from the mount command string or llog.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the server responds to a client, there&apos;s no need to lock the client&apos;s primary NID.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="81564">LU-17665</key>
            <summary>LNet: lock primary NID only on a peer constructed by Lustre</summary>
